
[1]brooch

   BROOCH, n. broche.

   1. An ornamental utensil for fastening the vest, or the bosom of a
   shirt, as formerly used in America. It is usually made of silver, often
   round, with a tongue crossing its diameter, sometimes with two tongues.
   It formerly was used in England, as it was in America, and is still in
   the highlands of Scotland.

   2. A jewel.

   3. With painters, a painting all of one color.

          BROOCH, v.t. To adorn or furnish with brooches or jewels.
